teBuffer())\n                .withMessageContaining(\"Illegal string length\");\n        assertThatExceptionOfType(IllegalArgumentException.class)\n                .isThrownBy(() -> new Message(Map.of(\"empty-bytes\", HeaderValue.fromByteArray(new byte[0])),\n                        new byte[0]).toByteBuffer())\n                .withMessageContaining(\"Byte arrays may not be empty\");\n        assertThatExceptionOfType(IllegalArgumentException.class)\n                .isThrownBy(() -> new Message(Map.of(\"long-bytes\", HeaderValue.fromByteArray(new byte[32_768])),\n                        new byte[0]).toByteBuffer())\n                .withMessageContaining(\"Illegal byte array length\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void decodeHonorsCurrentByteBufferPositionAndAdvancesToMessageEnd() {"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Testing bounds validation**\n\nI'm thinking about testing bounds validation for encoding and decoding, specifically checking if empty strings or byte arrays are allowed. It seems like the current implementation only handles null values and not invalid lengths. The feature related to the event stream format appears to enforce constraints, but we should test the public API as well. I want to make sure that constructors are validating inputs and throwing exceptions as needed. I might also consider whether to add tests for malformed header types or if that’s just corruption.\n\n**Exploring collection methods**\n\nI'm considering using `Map.entry` with the existing `LinkedHashMap` for some repeated assertions, avoiding direct reflection or serialization, which is a relief. I think it's important we ensure everything is accessible for compiling with repeated calls, probably targeting Java 11 or even JDK 21. It seems `Map.of` is already in use, which is good. I should also add an assertion method to handle illegal argument exceptions as part of our tests for header encoding. Lastly, I’ll clearly define limits for string lengths as needed.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0897e6bbbb4b000d0169f783c0c7a08192b4fa4fd327f8c451\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp94PMQw-R1oeLEDNgNbpTJovvtzl3oJQD84ZGNhx-SmqpfbwuPY7yoQuRw_aF2OvCw2SgUc7QphiDYKsTv5V4L5pXzfppObbYGpt8sLnqZhY-ownyGnm9skeOh2bEg8BccSv2YQ2EVdok6J0-iWYejeH5UEtPsUOlHMAotoFN-5PAD2qxoDDnFF1E43zzeFuH_jVPTWEvP-teyz7EJAR3RZaqjU3NARa9fVHN5CDhVGPmTEYXH6aVsv10asrigBOWJR1h4GINstpa2EXBYiwfHGW5hj65xTD6Zmz0rDVjV-ZyN7W0D2R1LO9DnwfOaoEGvFfOQCHzntrOpc0IGxuI4B_IJC7wMJfcalqhhqSpjvCZxkDWmJftej2MV1LnZ78qnrPy3hsIMKKwVg9KO0VZF9AKJNsHuBR4r4I3SVTCvhRIL9LPCrSWCb9KFGZYfd5AVSMkWJHfezr5RUftka2eq82n_Ct6bltCn-QXu_4Ld5jHwdEJiU5bohHGenFqcl9IGokgDKrYEHr_Jouav5AmOkEX2tTykLnUvxlQpfSeiY9_yrdLUhvui3lzWLxHbpMLI9hgHwAvVkfRsBBwm